-- Minijos Nafta Plans First Lithuanian Shale-Gas Well This Year
-- B y   M i l d a   S e p u t y t e
-- 2012-01-18T11:27:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-18/minijos-nafta-plans-first-lithuanian-shale-gas-well-this-year.html
Minijos Nafta UAB, a Lithuanian oil
producer, plans to invest 10 million litai ($3.72 million) to
explore shale gas in the west of the Baltic nation.  The company, which has a license to search for shale gas,
plans to drill its first exploration well this year, the
Gargzdai-based company said today in a  statement  on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Milda Seputyte in Vilnius at 
 mseputyte@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
